headline.main: J.J. HILL DEAD. IN ST. PAUL HOME AT THE AGE OF 77; Noted Railroad Man and "Empire Builder" Passes Away After a Short Illness. FORTUNE PUT AT $75,000,000 6,000 Miles of Railroad a Monument to His Work ;- Large Interest in Ships and Banks. 60 YEARS IN NORTHWEST Rose from Clerk to Commanding Position in Business ;- Many Pay High Tribute to His Memory. J.J. HILL DEAD IN ST. PAUL HOME

snippet: ST. PAUL, May 29. -- James J. Hill, builder of the "Northwest Empire," died at 9:30 A.M. today at his house, 240 Summit Avenue.

byline.original: Special to The New York Times
